CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper September 25, 1943, pg. unknown, reads: "Joe Johns and His Boxing Troupe Visit Bedridden Soldiers at Veterans Hospital - On his way to Camp Shenango last Monday, Sgt. Joe Louis and his touring troupe of boxers stopped off at the Veteran's hospital in Butler to visit some of the inmates... Lower left: James Edgar, Jackie Fields, Joe Louis and Ray Robinson, all famous in the boxing world, pictured at the hospital.  Fields is a member of the athletic staff at Bulter...  Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Boxers James Edgar, Jackie Fields, Joe Louis, and Sugar Ray Robinson in military uniforms at Butler Veterans' Hospital
